This paper is about a neural network model for natural language processing tasks, specifically parsing and sentence understanding. The paper discusses techniques for combining these two tasks into a single model, which suggests that it is likely to be relevant to the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of batched computation and the speedup achieved by this technique, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its model on a natural language inference task, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), which often involves natural language processing tasks.
